values:
you are dimgray
#696969

Your dominant hue is red... you are passionate, energetic, and unafraid of life's changes. You're all about getting out and trying something new, even if it means taking risks that other people would be afraid of. Hey, if they're afraid and you're not, more power to you, right?

Your saturation level is very low - you have better things to do than jump headfirst into every little project. You make sure your actions are going to really accomplish something before you start because you hate wasting energy making everyone else think you're working.

Your outlook on life is slightly darker than most people's. You try to see things for what they are and face situations honestly. You'd rather get to the point than look for what's good.

Rachaell stayed the night last night. We didn't go to bed till' about 1am. The kid just wouldn't get tired! We made cookies last night, heart shaped ones, for my mom for Valentines day. We were too tired to finish so we carried it out to this morning. I'll mail them off tomorrow in this cute little red box :)
I went to my gpas house yesterday for a few hours and he tought me all about ranges. I can't wait till next week! I'm going out on my own as soon as the circuit boards come in.
Oh yeah, I'm getting sooo tan!! I'm SO excited *lol* I'm WEARING A BATHINGSUIT IN PUBLIC THIS SUMMER!!!
Anyhoo, gotta run. BYE

I started working for my grandpa yesterday. I'm so excited!!!! Appliance Repair Technician here I come!!!
We're supposed to go dancing tonight. Don't think I want to go. *yawn*
I might just tell Frank to go without me *lol* Maybe I'll stay home, have a drink, take a bath and watch a movie. Then go party like a rockstar. Probably not but sounded good :)
I changed my name by the way. If anyone is interested in knowing what it is, send me an email. If I know you, I'll tell you. If I don't, don't ask.
The reason was....basically to get away from certain people.
http://mjcutiepants.livejournal.com/3004.html

Starting today I'm taking over my own life. Not that anyone's been doing it for me, but there's so much going on that I feel like I have no control over. I want to go back to school, I want to go to the gym, I want to have a part time job so I have time to get my things done. By the way....not sure who else reads this but I got fired from my job. That was a kick in the teeth. Didn't have enough experience. Anyway, I wouldn't of been able to go to school with that job anyway. Such is life.
I want to get married someday. Let's be honest, I want to marry my boyfriend someday. I have thousands of dollars in bills I can't pay and I feel that my only option is to file bankruptcy. I don't want to do that. No one wants to marry someone that is so much in debt, and no one wants to marry someone that has a bankruptcy. I just don't know what direction I'm going to go in. Either way, I've got a list a mile long of things that I need to get done and I'm going to just do them...no putting anything off anymore. I'm doing it for me, for my girls and for my boyfriend. I love him so much. So, I'll be keeping up on here of what I've been able to get done, what I want to do and anything else I can think of.

Wow, it's been 7 months today for Frank and I. I can't believe it! We stayed up really late last night and I'm waaay tooo tiiired. Some friends and us are going to Harvy's tonight. Should be awesome! That's it for now, but I'll be back on soon.

So did my back, but that's starting to fade a little. Anyway, wow! I'm actually looking forward to going tomorrow! I can't believe it worked so well!!

They are 7 min. beds, and I got a free bottle of $45 accelerator! On top of that, Jenni got me a year membership at Bally's for Christmas! By my 1 year anniversary (5 mos from now) I'll be able to wear a bikinni :D Ok, prob not. But I'll look hella kickazzzz!!! Anyway, time to go tanning! BYEEEE

I've been thinking about changing my name. Yes, I'm thinking of jumping on the band wagon. The first time I ever thought about it, I was 15 years old and I liked the name Khorin. (korin). I've recently been partial to Madyson, Maddisen, or Maddison. I've never been into the tradition spelling of names. That's probably why both of my girls have somewhat different spellings of "Rebecca" and "Rachel". 
My friend Nate decided to tell me if I ever changed my name he would just call me Bill.
http://mjcutiepants.livejournal.com/1225.html

I haven't been on ski's since I was 15 years old. That's almost 10 years!! I'm so excited yet a little scared, since the reason I haven't gone up, is that I had knee surgery when I was 21. BUT, I've never been one to let anything like that stop me. Frank bought a new snowboard, and he's gonna be doing that for the day. I'm sure I won't get off the bunny hill. I rented ski's from GI Joes last night. They were only $16, compared to $25 on the mountain. I got some really nice ski pants, gloves, goggles, and I think I'm all set. I have a really nice camara case that attatches to my pants, so I'll be taking lots of pictures up there. We also had to buy chains last night at costco. They weren't very expensive though! Anyway, Frank made me coffee this morning, and when he brought it in, he said "Marsha, best girlfriend in the world, wake uppppppp" He's so cute. And he's all mine *lol*
OMG, then last night he was working on his snowboard, and I came out to the living room to luv on him for a while and he said "I love your smile sooooo much....I want a wife that smiles like that" lol then I said "ok good, you will!" :D
Anyway, we're headed out now. byeeee ~MJ~
http://mjcutiepants.livejournal.com/938.html

Last night, while we were getting into bed, I asked Frank "hey babe, can I ask you a serious question?" He said yes, of course. I said "do you think you would really be happy with me being the last girl you ever sleep with?" He was funny for a second, and said "yeah...you're pretty good in bed" ~lol~ Then he said, "yes of course". We've talked a little about our future, and what it might have in store for us. Sometimes a little serious, sometimes not. This morning I ran in the room and jumped on him, trying to wake him up. He kept saying I was cute. Then "I want a girlfriend that's cute all the time.. "I want a wife that's cute all the time".... Sometimes he says things like that. It makes me know that we're still on the same page with everything else that's going on in our lives.
I'm so in love with him. We used to argue. I used to walk around with a chip on my shoulder every day...most days were good...but a lot were just ok. Our days aren't just ok anymore. They are wonderful, and I'm so excited to know that the man I'm with is the one I want to be with for the rest of my life.

I need to go, but I'll write more later.
